54.9	The_Restaurant_at_the_End_of_the_Universe	The Restaurant at the End of the Universe	The Restaurant at the End of the Universe (1980, ISBN 0-345-39181-0) is the second book in the Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy comedy science fiction trilogy of five by Douglas Adams. It was originally published by Pan Books as a paperback. The book was inspired by the song "Grand Hotel" by British rock band Procol Harum. It takes its name from Milliways, the Restaurant at the End of the Universe, one of the settings of the book.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/98/RestaurantAtTheEndOfTheUniverse.jpg/200px-RestaurantAtTheEndOfTheUniverse.jpg
